LES Elementary

post_text: LCSC IS EXCITED TO ANNOUNCE THAT WE LEARNED THIS AFTERNOON THAT WE HAVE BEEN AWARDED A GRANT THAT WILL PROVIDE FREE BREAKFAST AND LUNCH TO ALL STUDENTS This, however, does not cover adult meals or a-la-carte items. This is a USDA grant and will run from tomorrow, September 10, through December 31st or until the grant money disappears. Loogootee Covid-Online Academy students also qualify and may contact Patti Sander at 812-295-3254, ext. 488 during school hours to make arrangements for pick up. Current money will remain in student accounts to be used for a-la-carte items or to be used after the grant funding is exhausted when normal pricing will resume. We encourage all students to participate in this program.

post_text: Today is Mrs. Donna Rayhill’s official last day at Loogootee Community Schools. In her career she has touched the lives of many kids and adults. She is a true gem and will be missed greatly. We wish her the very best in this next chapter of her life. Congratulations Mrs. Rayhill and enjoy retirement!

post_text: The Martin County Health Department has announced that the Indiana State Department of Health will be providing free COVID-19 testing at the Memorial Country Health Clinic on County Road 900 East (Cannelburg Road) in Daviess County. The free and confidential drive thru clinic will be today and tomorrow (8/28/20) from 9 am to 6 pm EST. ANYONE over the age of 2 years old can be COVID-19 tested.

post_text: PreK Registration for the 20-21 school year is open!
shared_text:
Loogootee Community Schools
May 14 at 11:42 AM ·

We are now accepting applications for the 2020-2021 school year. This is for our Lion's Den PreK. If you know any 4 or 5 year olds in the community please share the following information.
PreK is a half day class for students who are 4 years old by August 1st. This class is five days a week.
How to apply: Go to www.loogootee.k12.in.us. Click on "Our Schools" and look for Loogootee Elementary. Locate the Preschool tab and click on the registration link. You may fill the form our online or print it and mail it to Loogootee Elementary, 101 Costello Drive, Loogootee, IN 47553.
Thank you for helping us get the word out to the community. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to ask.
Online Form: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ED9jVMkoUn-5o2W2sbBSsyGg2ltotIH0R01syGsXa2U/copy
PDF Form: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1A-u82js-xkUv2WY0TdmLZuleOz_7ZFca/view?usp=sharing

post_text:
This is a reminder that FREE meals will be offered to every student in the Loogootee Community School Corporation. Information about picking up the meals is found below:

-Cafeteria personnel will provide FREE “grab and go” meals to all LCSC students who wish to participate during the closure period beginning Tuesday, March 17, 2020. All meals will be prepared at Loogootee High School with pick up in the front parking lot using a “drive-up” service between 11:00 a.m.-1:00 p.m. THERE WILL BE 10 MEALS IN EACH BAG (5 BREAKFASTS AND 5 LUNCHES). If you are not available to pick up food during this time, please call your school office and arrange for a time that we can provide the food for your child.

-Food will not be provided during the week of Spring Break, March 23-27.

-Food will be provided during the week of March 30-April 3 with the “drive-thru” pick up service available between 11:00 a.m. and 1:00 p.m. on Tuesday, March 31st. Again, call your school office to arrange a different time if needed.

Promote your school spirit and help raise money for Loogootee Schools by continuing to do what you do every day - swiping your check card for everyday purchases. The Loogootee Lions School Spirit Check Card offered by German American Bank is accepted everywhere Visa® is welcome:
• Grocery Stores
• Gas Stations
• Local Shops
• Department Stores
• And more!

Every time you use your Loogootee Lions School Spirit Check Card, German American Bank will donate $0.02 back to our school. Over time, the two cents per swipe can lead up to hundreds even thousands of dollars for the schools. Stop by any convenient German American Bank location to obtain your Loogootee Lions School Spirit Check Card today. If you already have a German American Check Card, just ask for a free upgrade to the Loogootee Lions School Spirit Check Card.

*School Spirit Check Card requires a German American checking account and approval of check card application.

Every time you use your Loogootee Lions School Spirit Check Card, German American Bank will donate $0.02 back to our school. Over time, the two cents per swipe can lead up to hundreds even thousands of dollars for the schools. Stop by any convenient German American Bank location to obtain your Loogootee Lions School Spirit Check Card today. If you already have a German American Check Card, just ask for a free upgrade to the Loogootee Lions School Spirit Check Card.

*School Spirit Check Card requires a German American checking account and approval of check card application.

post_text:
LCSC has decided to cancel Monday Night's "Meet and Greet" so that we can have a few more hours to put the finishing touches on our buildings before students arrive.

On Tuesday, we are going to open all buildings at 7:45 am and parents/guardians are invited to visit the schools with their child to meet teachers and see the classrooms.

Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work through this renovation project. We will have an "Open House" for our entire community once all renovations have been completed.
